SIMPLE: coupling
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Coupling
<hw>Coup"ling</hw> <pr>(-l?ng)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
act of bringing or coming together; connection; sexual union.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Mach.)</fld> <def>A device or contrivance which
serves to couple or connect adjacent parts or objects; <as>as, a belt
<ex>coupling</ex>, which connects the ends of a belt; a car
<ex>coupling</ex>, which connects the cars in a train; a shaft
<ex>coupling</ex>, which connects the ends of shafts</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><mcol><col><b>Box coupling</b></col>, <col><b>Chain
coupling</b></col></mcol>. <cd>See under <er>Box</er>, Chain.</cd> --
<col><b>Coupling box</b></col>, <cd>a coupling shaped like a journal
box, for clamping together the ends of two shafts, so that they may
revolve together.</cd> -- <col><b>Coupling pin</b></col>, <cd>a pin or
bolt used in coupling or joining together railroad cars,
etc.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Coupon</ent>⟦br⟧
